column24:
Dystrophic Red-Yellow Latosol is the predominant
 soil type. Chemical and physical analyses of the soil samples, conducted according
 to EMBRAPA (2009), Almeida et al. (2012) and Almeida and
 Sanches (2012), yielded the following values: pH (in H2O) = 6.48;
 P = 111.5 mg dm_3; K = 186.00 mg dm_3; Ca = 3.99 cmolc dm_3;
 Mg = 0.73 cmolc dm_3; N = 0.078 dag kg_1; OM = 2.50 dag kg_1;
 Al3+ = 0.00 cmolc dm_3; H + Al=1.50 cmolc dm_3; base Sum =
 5.20 cmolc dm_3; potential CEC=6.70 cmolc dm_3; base saturation=
 77.60%; sand= 396 g kg_1; silt = 145 g kg_1; and clay= 459 g kg_1.

